==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Arriere
<hw>Ar*riere"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>arri⟦egrave⟧re</ets>. See <er>Arrear</er>.]</ety> <def>⟦ldquo⟧That
which is behind⟦rdquo⟧; the rear; -- chiefly used as an adjective in the
sense of <xex>behind</xex>, <xex>rear</xex>,
<xex>subordinate</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Arriere fee</b></col>, <col><b>Arriere
fief</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a fee or fief dependent on a superior fee, or
a fee held of a feudatory.</cd> -- <col><b>Arriere vassal</b></col>,
<cd>the vassal of a vassal.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Arriere-ban</ent>⟦br⟧
